Dec 4 (Reuters) - Bitcoin dropped 8.4% to $49,228.82 at 20:01 GMT on Saturday, losing $4,514.87 from its previous close. Bitcoin, the world's biggest and best-known cryptocurrency, is down 28.7% from the year's high of $69,000 on Nov. 10. Ether , the coin linked to the ethereum blockchain network, dipped  2.69 % to $4,109.14 on Saturday, losing $113.66 from its previous close. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.